connections.name: Logan Baird
connections.notes: 7/9 - No open positions, but Logan submitted an in-house referral to company recruiters: "I've had the privilege of seeing Crystal in a number of different work roles over the years, but the commonalities have been that she A) knows how to manage projects (whether given to her or self-assigned), B) knows how to work well with a variety of people, and C) knows how to troubleshoot. She practiced those skills working for others, and refined them when she created and ran her own business. At her core, she's solution-oriented with a great eye for detail and understanding of process, which is why I was so excited when she started at Nashville Software School, a bootcamp in which she excelled and from which we've consistently hired over the years. Aside from that, I think she'd be an excellent culture fit, and would bring a lot of personality to the organization."

connections.name: Brent Eskew
connections.notes: 7/10 - Texted BJ about some open positions at Vaco. They don't have an internal referral program, but he said to put him down as a reference and he would follow up once I submitted my resume.
